column5: Is anyone throwing the Waxwing jigs for Musky? They have a really cool action, but that doesn't mean they will catch fish  I have thrown one a couple of times, but they weren't hitting anything, so it's tough for me to compare.
" Waxwing Freshwater version performs the best with new Tranx reel, Compre Musky rod and PowerPro Hollow-Ace with Flurocarbon leader. "   Sounds like they are trying to sell something?

I threw one for a few minutes that a friend bought, excellent action on it, similar to a Hellhound but you just do a straight retrieve with it. I don't fish glide/jerk baits much but I will probably have one in my box for next season.
